{% comment %}
  THE RUB PRODUCT PAGE — RECIPES MADE FOR THIS RUB
{% endcomment %}
<section class="recipes-section wrap">
  <div class="section-head">
    <span class="tape alt">From the test kitchen</span>
    <h2>Recipes made for this rub</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="recipes-grid">
    <div class="recipe-card">
      <div class="recipe-img"><span class="tape" style="font-size:13px; padding:8px 16px;">Grilling</span></div>
      <div class="recipe-body">
        <h3>Dry-rub grilled wings</h3>
        <p>High heat, one coat of rub, and the patience to not check them every 90 seconds.</p>
        <a href="the-rub-recipe-template.html" class="recipe-link">Get the recipe</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="recipe-card">
      <div class="recipe-img"><span class="tape" style="font-size:13px; padding:8px 16px;">Low and slow</span></div>
      <div class="recipe-body">
        <h3>Smoked rib rack</h3>
        <p>Rub it the night before. Let the fridge do some of the work for you.</p>
        <a href="#" class="recipe-link">Get the recipe</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="recipe-card">
      <div class="recipe-img"><span class="tape" style="font-size:13px; padding:8px 16px;">Weeknight</span></div>
      <div class="recipe-body">
        <h3>Sheet-pan potatoes</h3>
        <p>Olive oil, a heavy hand with the rub, 425 degrees. Done before you finish a beer.</p>
        <a href="#" class="recipe-link">Get the recipe</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
